<h1>2016 American Astronomical Society WorldWide Telescope Competition</h1>
<p>The American Astronomical Society and Explore Scientific are excited to announce the results of the 2016 WWT Prize.  Tours were judged in three categories: <strong>Research</strong>, <strong>Education</strong> or <strong>Planetarium</strong>, with a grand prize and special 2017 eclipse prize.</p>
<p>We had great tours submitted and are pleased to announce the 2016 winners.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>Planetarium</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>First Place</strong> - <a href="/Community/#/ContentDetail/81795">Eclipse: Countdown to Totality (Beau Hartweg)</a></li>
    <li><strong>Second Place</strong> - <a href="/Community/#/ContentDetail/81796">Earth Day VR (David Weigel)</a></li>
    <li><strong>Third Place</strong> - <a href="/Community/#/ContentDetail/81797">A Solar System Perspective (Christina Moraitis) </a></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Education</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>First Place</strong> - <a href="/Community/#/ContentDetail/81801">Moon Phases Lab (Patricia Udomprasert)</a></li>
    <li><strong>Second Place</strong> - <a href="/Community/#/ContentDetail/81802">New Horizons: Mission to Pluto (Sumiyyah Jalalyar) </a></li>
    <li><strong>Third Place</strong> - <a href="/Community/#/ContentDetail/81803">A Parallax Lab for Astronomy 101 Classes (Ned Ladd) </a></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>Research</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>First Place</strong> - <a href="/Community/#/ContentDetail/81794">Planet Nine Video Abstract (Konstantin Batygin)</a></li>
</ul><p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>2016 Grand Prize</h4>
<ul>
    <li><a href="/Community/#/ContentDetail/81804">Transiting Exoplanets - Life in the Universe (Harry Houghton)</a></li>
</ul><p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>Special Eclipse 2017 Prize</h4>
<ul>
    <li><a href="/Community/#/ContentDetail/81795">Eclipse: Countdown to Totality (Beau Hartweg) </a></li>
</ul>
