<h3>Prizes</h3>
<p>There will be a first, second and third place prize in each category donated by the <a href="http://aas.org">American Astronomical Society</a> and <a href="http://explorescientificusa.com/">Explore Scientific</a>.&nbsp; Details on the prizes are coming soon!</p>
<h3>Entry Instructions</h3>
<p>Fill out the entry form at: <a href="http://wwtworkshops.org/">http://wwtworkshops.org/</a></p>
<h3>WWT Prize Submission</h3>
<p><a href="http://wwtworkshops.org/"><img alt="WWT Prize Submission" src="@Model.ImgDir/news/wwt-prize-submission.jpg" class="img-responsive" /></a></p>
<p>At the prize website you will have to create an account.&nbsp; This will allow you to manage your entries and for us to know to contact you if you win!&nbsp;</p>
<p>Submissions require you to select Category (<strong>Research</strong>, <strong>Education</strong> or <strong>Planetarium</strong>) and Format (<strong>Tour</strong>, <strong>Interactive</strong> or <strong>Video</strong>).&nbsp; You will also need to provide a title for your submission.</p>
<p>All submissions need to be on-line.&nbsp; If you are submitting a YouTube video or web interactive, you simply need to copy the URL to the on-line video or interactive and paste that into the entry website.&nbsp; You re all done!</p>
<p>If you have a WTT Tour you will provide the Tour Title in the entry site.&nbsp; You will first need to upload the tour into your private community through the WWT Community mechanism.&nbsp; Instructions on using communities is available here: <a href="/Learn/Authoring#usingcommunities">http://www.worldwidetelescope.org/Learn/Authoring#usingcommunities</a></p>
<p>Detailed instructions are given below.</p>
<ol>
    <li>Get a Live ID:</li>
    <li>Go to the WWT home page: <a href="/home">http://www.worldwidetelescope.org/home</a></li>
    <li>
